parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch wiring harness can cause the headlights to shut off while driving, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights flicker on and off
headlights shut off while driving
headlights do not come back on for several seconds
fog lights cause all lights to go out
headlight switch gets very hot
dash above headlight switch melts
plastic pigtail in wiring starts to catch fire and melt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the occupant in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt does not hold tension
the seat belt buckle does not close
the seat belt latch does not release
the seat belt has unraveled and will not retract.
